- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another likely category as the paper discusses a variant of the classic VASS model, which is a data structure used in algorithmic verification. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper deals with automata models and their connections with timed automata. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of a problem that arises in the context of program verification. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper investigates the complexity of a reachability problem in a specific automata model.
